text.tspan: Share of US land area with unusually low winter temperatures
Unusually cold winter temperatures are measured based on daily minimum temperatures. At each station, the recorded lows are compared
with the full set of historical records. After averaging over a particular month or season of interest, the coldest 10 percent of years are defined
Data source: National Oceanic & Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) via the US EPA
